main event: A white light object was observed in the sky, blinking and hovering, tracked by ground radar on July 1, 1962.
interesting points: The object was tracked by ground radar for 24 minutes., Air intercept radar was unable to track the object., The object rapidly departed the area, suggesting it could be a missile-type vehicle., The sighting was reported at 2330Z., There was no verification to determine if the object was airborne or on the ground.
sighted object: white light object in the sky
witness description: no witnesses described in the report
